{
  "stem": "27509.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were-- they were sitting there like sitting ducks, even when at-- at-- even those who have left Poland to went to Lithuania to-- to escape the immediate war thought that by going away from Poland to Lithuania to Vilna, which was already then handed over by the Russians to as the capital of Lithuania, they thought, it's far enough to outlive the war years there.",
      "word_count": 66
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So short-sighted and so naive were the people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they were people who were otherwise were business people and smart people and so on.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they wouldn't budge.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They wouldn't even try and attempt to get the visa.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Didn't want to go way too far from home because they've left factories behind.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They've left real estate behind.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They've left things like that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they didn't budge.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they-- and they perished.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was-- it was a matter of-- of just utterances of-- of-- of individual pessimism.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It-- it was only a matter how pessimistic one was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I, for one, strangely enough, took very early a very pessimistic view.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember-- and that maybe answers some of the very early questions that you have asked me about my relationship with my father.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After the Germans came in first time and left and handed over to the Russians, and the Russians-- and then-- and then there was a moment when everybody was buying everything because the money was losing [INAUDIBLE] value and so.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I pleaded with my father and said, you lived through a war.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You were-- all right.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a different Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But you were occupied by the Germans in the First World War.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
